subSubSection.paragraph:
Description of genitalia.
Pygophore (
Figs. 10E
, 
17G, H
) compressed dorsoventrally, hexagonal in ventral view, strongly concave at anterior margin of dorsum, elevated at center of venter, smooth on surface, irregularly punctate in middle part of dorsum. Paramere (
Fig. 18G, H
) expanded in middle part, curved inward in apical part; outer and inner margins covered with pubescence in middle part. Female terminalia (
Fig. 11E
) pentagonal in ventral view, covered with pubescence.

